BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:proac-jogos-eletronicos-05-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T083341Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260727
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260728
SUMMARY:Deadline: ProAC / Fomento CultSP: Edital 05/2026\, Electronic Games
  Development and Publishing
DESCRIPTION:Sao Paulo state's ProAC scheme runs one of the largest dedicate
 d public funds for game development in Latin America. Edital 05/2026 split
 s BRL 6\,000\,000 across two modules of ten projects each: Module I for de
 veloping electronic games\, Module II for finalising and publishing them\,
  at BRL 300\,000 per project. At least six of the ten slots in each module
  are reserved for applicants based outside the state capital. ELIGIBILITY 
 IS RESTRICTED AND NARROW: individuals cannot apply. Applicants must be leg
 al entities\, meaning private companies (for-profit or not-for-profit) or 
 registered MEI microentrepreneurs\, headquartered in Sao Paulo state for a
 t least two years\, with artistic or cultural activity expressly stated in
  their founding documents. Applications close 27 July 2026 at 23:59:59 Bra
 silia time via fomento.sp.gov.br. Note this is a tight deadline.\n\nOrgani
 sation: Secretaria da Cultura\, Economia e Industria Criativas do Estado d
 e Sao Paulo (ProAC)\nLocation: Sao Paulo state\, Brazil. Open only to lega
 l entities headquartered in Sao Paulo state for at least two years.\nAward
 : BRL 300\,000 (around USD 55\,000 / EUR 50\,000) per selected project\, 2
 0 projects total across two modules\, from a BRL 6\,000\,000 pool. Registr
 ation is free.\nDuration: Module I funds game development\; Module II fund
 s finalisation and publishing of an existing game.\n\nMore: https://www.cu
 ltura.sp.gov.br/sec_cultura/Arquivo_de_Editais/Editais_Fomento_Cultsp/Fome
 nto_CultSP_2026/desenvolvimento_ou_finalizacao_e_publicacao_de_jogos_eletr
 onicos_2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.cultura.sp.gov.br/sec_cultura/Arquivo_de_Editais/Editais_Fo
 mento_Cultsp/Fomento_CultSP_2026/desenvolvimento_ou_finalizacao_e_publicac
 ao_de_jogos_eletronicos_2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_me
 dium=referral
LOCATION:Sao Paulo state\, Brazil. Open only to legal entities headquartere
 d in Sao Paulo state for at least two years.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:instituto-sacatar-fellowship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T083341Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260828
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260829
SUMMARY:Deadline: Instituto Sacatar: Sacatar Fellowship 2027 (Bahia\, Brazi
 l)
DESCRIPTION:Brazil's longest-running artist residency\, on the island of It
 aparica across the bay from Salvador\, hosting six to eight artists per se
 ssion for roughly eight weeks. Open to all creative disciplines and\, unus
 ually for this region\, to all nationalities\, which makes it one of the f
 ew genuinely international residencies in Latin America. Sacatar provides 
 full hosting (private room\, three meals daily\, individual studio\, laund
 ry\, local logistics and connections) but explicitly does NOT provide a st
 ipend\, airfare to Salvador\, art materials or discretionary local expense
 s\, so applicants must fund their own travel. Individual artists only\; gr
 oup proposals are not accepted and former Sacatar Fellows may not reapply.
  COVID vaccination is required. NOTE: there is a USD 25 application fee. A
 pply through SlideRoom by 28 August 2026. Contact info@sacatar.org.\n\nOrg
 anisation: Instituto Sacatar\nLocation: Itaparica island\, Bahia\, Brazil.
  Open to all nationalities.\nAward: Fully hosted residency: private bedroo
 m with attached bathroom\, three meals a day (except Saturday evenings\, S
 undays and Brazilian holidays)\, an individual studio suited to the discip
 line\, weekly laundry\, logistical support and airport transfer from Salva
 dor. NO STIPEND\, no airfare and no materials budget. USD 25 application f
 ee. One French artist may additionally receive airfare and a stipend throu
 gh Villa Fatumbi.\nDuration: Approximately eight weeks\; specific session 
 dates are listed in the application.\n\nMore: https://sacatar.org/en/fello
 wships/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://sacatar.org/en/fellowships/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantde
 sk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Itaparica island\, Bahia\, Brazil. Open to all nationalities.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:red-quincho-beca-constelaciones-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T083341Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260809
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260810
SUMMARY:Deadline: Red Quincho: Beca Constelaciones 2026 (4th Edition)
DESCRIPTION:Beca Constelaciones is Red Quincho's mobility and production gr
 ant for artists\, curators and researchers doing territory-based work\, no
 w in its fourth edition. Each recipient spends one month in residence\, sp
 lit into two 15-day placements at different member spaces across Argentina
 \, pairing an urban and a rural context. The grant covers mobility\, livin
 g costs and production\, with lodging provided. Backed by Fundacion Willia
 ms\, CCEBA and Fundacion Santander through the CABA Mecenazgo scheme. ELIG
 IBILITY IS RESTRICTED: of the 15 grants\, 13 are for people resident in Ar
 gentina and 2 are for people currently living in Spain. Artists\, curators
  and researchers apply through separate forms\; Spanish-based candidates f
 ace an additional jury evaluation. Deadline 9 August 2026 at 23:59 Argenti
 na time.\n\nOrganisation: Red Quincho\nLocation: Rotating urban and rural 
 Red Quincho spaces across Argentina\; residency runs September to December
  2026.\nAward: ARS 1\,000\,000 (around USD 690) per grant toward mobility\
 , living costs and production\, plus one month of lodging. 15 grants avail
 able. No application fee.\nDuration: One-month residency split into two 15
 -day placements at different spaces.\n\nMore: https://redquincho.ar/beca-c
 onstelaciones-2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=refer
 ral
URL:https://redquincho.ar/beca-constelaciones-2026/?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Rotating urban and rural Red Quincho spaces across Argentina\; res
 idency runs September to December 2026.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:premio-klemm-artes-visuales-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T083341Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260904
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260905
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fundacion Klemm: 29th Premio Klemm a las Artes Visuales 2
 026
DESCRIPTION:The Premio Klemm is one of Argentina's longest-running visual a
 rts prizes\, now in its 29th edition\, awarded by the Fundacion Federico J
 orge Klemm in Buenos Aires. It is notable for a genuinely open definition 
 of medium: the entry categories explicitly include arte digital\, robotica
 \, video\, videoinstalacion\, audio and fotografia alongside painting\, dr
 awing and sculpture\, so technology-based practice is squarely in scope. E
 ntrants submit one work dated 2021 or later\, which must be durable rather
  than ephemeral. The top prizes are acquisition prizes\, so winning work e
 nters the foundation's collection. ELIGIBILITY IS RESTRICTED: Argentine na
 tionals (native or naturalised) or foreigners holding at least two years o
 f legal residence in Argentina\, aged 18 or over. Submissions close 4 Sept
 ember 2026 at 23:59. Prize amounts and the closing date are stated in the 
 bases y condiciones PDF linked from the entry site.\n\nOrganisation: Funda
 cion Federico Jorge Klemm\nLocation: Buenos Aires\, Argentina. Open to Arg
 entine nationals and to foreigners with at least two years of legal reside
 nce in Argentina.\nAward: First acquisition prize ARS 7\,000\,000 (around 
 USD 4\,800)\, second prize ARS 4\,000\,000 (around USD 2\,750). No entry f
 ee\; the foundation pays transport of selected works.\nDuration: Single pr
 ize with exhibition\; submitted work must be dated 2021 or later.\n\nMore:
  https://premioklemm.klemm.org.ar?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&ut
 m_medium=referral
URL:https://premioklemm.klemm.org.ar?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&
 utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Buenos Aires\, Argentina. Open to Argentine nationals and to forei
 gners with at least two years of legal residence in Argentina.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:proimagenes-fdc-estimulos-automaticos-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T083341Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261211
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261212
SUMMARY:Deadline: Proimagenes Colombia: FDC 2026 Estimulos Automaticos
DESCRIPTION:The Fondo para el Desarrollo Cinematografico\, created by Colom
 bia's Law 814 of 2003 and administered by Proimagenes Colombia\, channels 
 at least 70 percent of its resources into film production. The automatic s
 timuli are the non-competitive strand: rather than pitching against other 
 projects\, applicants qualify by meeting defined criteria. Six lines are o
 pen for 2026\, all closing 11 December 2026: film distribution in theatres
 \, Colombian shorts and features selected for approved festivals\, films n
 ominated for approved awards\, projects selected for approved industry enc
 ounters\, individuals selected for approved training workshops and advisor
 ies\, and promotion of national features or coproductions of at least 70 m
 inutes premiering in 2026. A separate competitive strand (estimulos por co
 ncurso) runs 17 modalities on its own calendar. ELIGIBILITY IS RESTRICTED:
  Colombian natural persons and Colombian legal entities\, though a Colombi
 an company may have a foreign legal representative. Contact convocatoriafd
 c@proimagenescolombia.com.\n\nOrganisation: Proimagenes Colombia (Fondo pa
 ra el Desarrollo Cinematografico)\nLocation: Colombia. Open to Colombian n
 atural persons and Colombian legal entities only.\nAward: Six automatic-st
 imulus lines drawn from the FDC's 2026 pool of roughly COP 21\,900 million
  (around USD 5.5 million). The feature film promotion line alone carries C
 OP 3\,620 million. Amounts per award are set per line. No application fee.
 \nDuration: Applies to activities taking place during 2026\; automatic sti
 muli are awarded on qualification rather than by competition.\n\nMore: htt
 ps://www.convocatoriafdc.com/estimulos-automaticos?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.convocatoriafdc.com/estimulos-automaticos?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Colombia. Open to Colombian natural persons and Colombian legal en
 tities only.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fundacion-ama-amoedo-grants-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T083341Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260909
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260910
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fundacion Ama Amoedo Grants 2026 (4th edition)
DESCRIPTION:The Fundacion Ama Amoedo Grants provide resources and opportuni
 ties to strengthen the visual arts ecosystem and its institutions. Through
  an open call\, ten grants of USD 10\,000 are awarded annually across four
  categories: Artists\, Art and Social Engagement\, Organizations\, and Pub
 lications. The program supports the realization of projects by artists\, o
 rganizations\, and institutions with a meaningful connection to Latin Amer
 ica. This is the 4th edition of the grants\; the Foundation receives appli
 cations via its online platform from 7 July to 9 September 2026. ELIGIBILI
 TY: artists\, collectives\, art professionals\, non-profit organizations\,
  institutions\, and foundations with a significant connection to Latin Ame
 rica\, whether through nationality\, cultural heritage\, and/or the locati
 on where the project will take place. Refer to the Terms and Conditions do
 cument on the website for full details. Inquiries: info@fundacionamaamoedo
 .org. Application deadline: Wednesday 9 September 2026\, 11:59 pm.\n\nOrga
 nisation: Fundacion Ama Amoedo\nLocation: Open to applicants with a signif
 icant connection to Latin America\, through nationality\, cultural heritag
 e\, and/or the location where the project takes place.\nAward: Ten grants 
 of USD 10\,000 each\, awarded annually across four categories: Artists\, A
 rt and Social Engagement\, Organizations\, and Publications. No applicatio
 n fee mentioned.\nDuration: Applications accepted via the online platform 
 from 7 July to 9 September 2026.\n\nMore: https://www.fundacionamaamoedo.o
 rg/programas/becas?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referr
 al
URL:https://www.fundacionamaamoedo.org/programas/becas?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Open to applicants with a significant connection to Latin America\
 , through nationality\, cultural heritage\, and/or the location where the 
 project takes place.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mar-del-plata-film-festival-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260724T083341Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: 41st Mar del Plata International Film Festival: Call for 
 Entries
DESCRIPTION:The Mar del Plata International Film Festival is the only FIAPF
  A-list competitive festival in Latin America. The 41st edition accepts in
 ternational entries across all genres for its International and Latin Amer
 ican competitions\, the In Transit work-in-progress section\, and Panorama
 . Films must be completed between November 2025 and November 2026 and not 
 previously publicly screened in Argentina. Extended deadline 15 July 2026\
 ; submissions via the INCAA portal.\n\nOrganisation: Festival Internaciona
 l de Cine de Mar del Plata / INCAA\nLocation: Mar del Plata\, Argentina (f
 estival 5-15 November 2026). Open to international entries\; no prior publ
 ic screening in Argentina.\nAward: Selection in Latin America's only FIAPF
  A-accredited competitive festival (International and Latin American compe
 titions\, In Transit/WIP\, Panorama). No submission fee stated on the regi
 stration page.\nDuration: Festival 5-15 November 2026. Films completed Nov
 ember 2025 to November 2026.\n\nMore: https://mardelplatafilmfest.com/41/e
 n/registrations/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://mardelplatafilmfest.com/41/en/registrations/?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Mar del Plata\, Argentina (festival 5-15 November 2026). Open to i
 nternational entries\; no prior public screening in Argentina.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
